<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1440,151,608]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[322,596,332,357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Uristidae" genus="Parschisturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[322,596,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Parschisturella carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most distinctive species in the genus because of the parachelate first gnathopod with its serrate palm. It is the only species with a distict constriction on the outer ramus of uropod 2. It shares a rounded boss on urosomite 1 with the Ausralian species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowry &amp; Kilgallen" authorityYear="2014" box="[929,1081,404,429]" class="Malacostraca" family="Uristidae" genus="Parschisturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martrudan">
<emphasis box="[929,1081,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. martrudan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1144,1235,404,429]" class="Malacostraca" family="Uristidae" genus="Parschisturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piloti">
<emphasis box="[1144,1235,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. piloti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It shares a well developed spine on the posteroventral corner of epimeron 3 with the Australian species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowry &amp; Kilgallen" authorityYear="2014" box="[1199,1351,439,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Uristidae" genus="Parschisturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martrudan">
<emphasis box="[1199,1351,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. martrudan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowry &amp; Kilgallen" authorityYear="2014" class="Malacostraca" family="Uristidae" genus="Parschisturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. medora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
